The National Working Committee (NWC) of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has updated its timetable and schedule of activities for the 2023 general elections. In the updated PDP 2023 timetable, the Local Government Area (LGA) Congress to elect one National Delegate per LGA and one person living with disability in the 774 local government areas now holds Tuesday, May 10, 2022. While the State House of Assembly (State Constituency Congress) will hold on Wednesday, May 18, 2022 PDP in a statement by its National Publicity Secretary, Hon. Debo Ologunagba, Wednesday also revealed that the House of Representatives Primaries is expected to hold Friday, May 20, 2022. According to the statement, the Senatorial District Primaries will be held on Saturday, May 21, 2022. Then Governorship Primaries will hold Monday, May 23, 2022. “All aspirants to various positions, critical stakeholders, members of our Party across the country as well as relevant agencies of government should please take note,” the statement read.